  Key Concurrency Points to Say in Interview
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
  ▎ "Each Showtime has its own threading.Lock. When book_seats acquires it, I first expire stale holds, then validate all-or-nothing, then atomically flip all seats to BOOKED. The lock is released at end of 
  the with block — even if an exception occurs — because Python's with calls __exit__ in the finally path. Two users racing for the same seat: one acquires the lock first, books it, releases. The second      
  acquires the lock, calls _expire_holds, sees the seat is BOOKED, returns None. Exactly one winner guaranteed."
                                                                                                                                                                                                                
